review_blob: Out of 12 oz. bottle in pint glass. Nice deep yellow color. Nice hop flavor, very bitter. Semi-long finish.
22oz bomber. Nice aroma, amber color, okay head. Flavors abound, although alcohol seeps through. Good American strong ale.
Nice pour, head, and color. but too flowery for my taste. Would have like deeper flavor.
From 33cl bottle into chalice. Nice head, although it did not last as long as I would have wanted. Wonderful aroma and flavor, with a medium long finish.
Poured from 12oz. bottle into tulip glass. Good color, head and aroma. Cherry flavors dominate aroma and taste. Decent finish.
What a way to celebrate 10 years. In tulip glass from bomber. Multiple flavors (not sure if I would recognize all 10 malts and hops, but well blended). Nice finish.
beer_name: HeBrew Monumental Jewbelation Tenth Anniversary Ale

review_blob: Out of bottle into chalice glass. Nice color and head. Unique aroma and taste; multiple flavors. Long finish.
Excellent Imperial Stout. Poured from bottle into tulip glass. Strong roasted flavors, with strong hints of chocolate. Long finish.
Rich golden color. From bottle in tulip glass. Nice hop flavor, but not too hoppy. Long finish. One of best IPAs.
Wow. Much fuller than unoaked. Chocolate flavors in addition to roasted flavors. Long finish. One of better Imperial stouts. The Russians would be proud.
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Oak Aged

review_blob: Excellent beer. Out of 750 bottle into chalice. Nice head, retained throughout drinking. Medium amber color. Flavors abound.
Out of bottle, tulip glass, nice color and head. Very roasty, multitude of flavors. Long finish. Excellent beer from the dark beer specialists.
Out of bottle in chalice. Poured with nice head. Roasted flavors, chocolate. Excellent finish.

From bottle in tulip glass. Pour well with good head, but quickly disappeared. Nose is flat. Medium roasted malt flavors. Fairly long finish (more than I expected for a beer like this). Not the best porter Ive had, but not the worst either.
Bottle. Tulip glass. Thick head and good mouth feel. Very dark. Good aroma, roasted flavors. Lingering.
Bottle. Watery flavor, bitterness on the end. Best thing about this beer is the appearance, which is quite pale and light.

Bottle. Nice deep color with good head. Highly carbonated at first, but lessened as beer sat (and warmed). Very smooth for such a strong brew. Tastes of malt, clove, and a hint of bananas on the finish.
